name: Name
welcome_message_description: A message that is displayed on the login page.
preferred_hardware_device_description: Applies only to VAAPI and QSV. Sets the dri node used for hardware transcoding.
tone_mapping_description: Attempts to preserve the appearance of HDR videos when converted to SDR. Each algorithm makes different tradeoffs for color, detail and brightness. Hable preserves detail, Mobius preserves color, and Reinhard preserves brightness.
storage_label_claim_description: Automatically set the user's storage label to the value of this claim.
storage_quota_claim_description: Automatically set the user's storage quota to the value of this claim.
custom_css_description: Cascading Style Sheets allow the design of Immich to be customized.
tone_mapping_npl_description: Colors will be adjusted to look normal for a display of this brightness. Counter-intuitively, lower values increase the brightness of the video and vice versa since it compensates for the brightness of the display. 0 sets this value automatically.
preset_preset_description: Compression speed. Slower presets produce smaller files, and increase quality when targeting a certain bitrate. VP9 ignores speeds above `faster`.
external_domain_description: Domain for public shared links, including http(s)://
target_resolution_description: Higher resolutions can preserve more detail but take longer to encode, have larger file sizes, and can reduce app responsiveness.
max_b_frames_description: Higher values improve compression efficiency, but slow down encoding. May not be compatible with hardware acceleration on older devices. 0 disables B-frames, while -1 sets this value automatically.
threads_description: Higher values lead to faster encoding, but leave less room for the server to process other tasks while active. This value should not be more than the number of CPU cores. Maximizes utilization if set to 0.
transcoding_disabled_description: Don't transcode any videos, may break playback on some clients
email_host_description: Host of the email server (e.g. smtp.immich.app)
constant_quality_mode_description: ICQ is better than CQP, but some hardware acceleration devices do not support this mode. Setting this option will prefer the specified mode when using quality-based encoding. Ignored by NVENC as it does not support ICQ.
quality_description: Image quality from 1-100. Higher is better for quality but produces larger files.
max_recognition_distance_description: Maximum distance between two faces to be considered the same person, ranging from 0-2. Lowering this can prevent labeling two people as the same person, while raising it can prevent labeling the same person as two different people. Note that it is easier to merge two people than to split one person in two, so err on the side of a lower threshold when possible.
max_detection_distance_description: Maximum distance between two images to consider them duplicates, ranging from 0.001-0.1. Higher values will detect more duplicates, but may result in false positives.
min_detection_score_description: Minimum confidence score for a face to be detected from 0-1. Lower values will detect more faces but may result in false positives.
facial_recognition_model_description: Models are listed in descending order of size. Larger models are slower and use more memory, but produce better results. Note that you must re-run the Face Detection job for all images upon changing a model.
delete_delay_description: Number of days after removal to permanently delete a user's account and assets. The user deletion job runs at midnight to check for users that are ready for deletion. Changes to this setting will be evaluated at the next execution.
number_of_days_description: Number of days to keep the assets in trash before permanently removing them
slideshow_duration_description: Number of seconds to display each image
audio_codec_description: Opus is the highest quality option, but has lower compatibility with old devices or software.
email_password_description: Password to use when authenticating with the email server
transcode_policy_description: Policy for when a video should be transcoded. HDR videos will always be transcoded (except if transcoding is disabled).
email_port_description: Port of the email server (e.g 25, 465, or 587)
default_storage_quota_description: Quota in GiB to be used when no claim is provided (Enter 0 for unlimited quota).
accepted_audio_codecs_description: Select which audio codecs do not need to be transcoded. Only used for certain transcode policies.
accepted_video_codecs_description: Select which video codecs do not need to be transcoded. Only used for certain transcode policies.
email_from_address_description: Sender email address, for example: "Immich Photo Server <noreply@immich.app>"
max_keyframe_interval_description: Sets the maximum frame distance between keyframes. Lower values worsen compression efficiency, but improve seek times and may improve quality in scenes with fast movement. 0 sets this value automatically.
max_bitrate_description: Setting a max bitrate can make file sizes more predictable at a minor cost to quality. At 720p, typical values are 2600k for VP9 or HEVC, or 4500k for H.264. Disabled if set to 0.
acceleration_api_description: The API that will interact with your device to accelerate transcoding. This setting is 'best effort': it will fallback to software transcoding on failure. VP9 may or may not work depending on your hardware.
min_recognized_faces_description: The minimum number of recognized faces for a person to be created. Increasing this makes Facial Recognition more precise at the cost of increasing the chance that a face is not assigned to a person.
reference_frames_description: The number of frames to reference when compressing a given frame. Higher values improve compression efficiency, but slow down encoding. 0 sets this value automatically.
machine_learning_url_description: URL of the machine learning server
map_style_setting_description: URL to a style.json map theme
preview_resolution_setting_description: Used when viewing a single photo and for machine learning. Higher resolutions can preserve more detail but take longer to encode, have larger file sizes, and can reduce app responsiveness.
thumbnail_resolution_description: Used when viewing groups of photos (main timeline, album view, etc.). Higher resolutions can preserve more detail but take longer to encode, have larger file sizes, and can reduce app responsiveness.
email_username_description: Username to use when authenticating with the email server
video_codec_description: VP9 has high efficiency and web compatibility, but takes longer to transcode. HEVC performs similarly, but has lower web compatibility. H.264 is widely compatible and quick to transcode, but produces much larger files. AV1 is the most efficient codec but lacks support on older devices.
constant_rate_factor_crf_description: Video quality level. Typical values are 23 for H.264, 28 for HEVC, 31 for VP9, and 35 for AV1. Lower is better, but produces larger files.
thumbnail_format_description: WebP produces smaller files than JPEG, but is slower to encode.
log_level_description: When enabled, what log level to use.
sidecar_job_description: Discover or synchronize sidecar metadata from the filesystem
metadata_extraction_job_description: Extract metadata information from each asset, such as GPS and resolution
thumbnail_generation_job_description: Generate large, small and blurred thumbnails for each asset, as well as thumbnails for each person
theme_settings_description: Manage customization of the Immich web interface
machine_learning_settings_description: Manage machine learning features and settings
map_settings_description: Manage map related features and setting
authentication_settings_description: Manage password, OAuth, and other authentication settings
storage_template_description: Manage the folder structure and file name of the upload asset
image_settings_description: Manage the quality and resolution of generated images
video_transcoding_settings_description: Manage the resolution and encoding information of the video files
migration_job_description: Migrate thumbnails for assets and faces to the latest folder structure
duplicate_detection_job_description: Run machine learning on assets to detect similar images. Relies on Smart Search
smart_search_job_description: Run machine learning on assets to support smart search
video_conversion_job_description: Transcode videos for wider compatibility with browsers and devices
hardware_decoding_setting_description: Applies only to NVENC and RKMPP. Enables end-to-end acceleration instead of only accelerating encoding. May not work on all videos.
temporal_aq_description: Applies only to NVENC. Increases quality of high-detail, low-motion scenes. May not be compatible with older devices.
auto_register_description: Automatically register new users after signing in with OAuth
theme_selection_description: Automatically set the theme to light or dark based on your browser's system preference
facial_recognition_description: Detect, recognize and group faces in images
people_sidebar_description: Display a link to People in the sidebar
sharing_sidebar_description: Display a link to Sharing in the sidebar
version_check_enabled_description: Enable periodic requests to GitHub to check for new releases
loop_videos_description: Enable to automatically loop a video in the detail viewer.
mobile_redirect_uri_override_description: Enable when 'app.immich:/' is an invalid redirect URI.
hash_verification_enabled_description: Enables hash verification, don't disable this unless you're certain of the implications
hardware_acceleration_description: Experimental; much faster, but will have lower quality at the same bitrate
custom_locale_description: Format dates and numbers based on the language and the region
default_locale_description: Format dates and numbers based on your browser locale
machine_learning_enabled_description: If disabled, all ML features will be disabled regardless of the below settings.
duplicate_detection_enabled_description: If disabled, exactly identical assets will still be de-duplicated.
facial_recognition_setting_description: If disabled, images will not be encoded for facial recognition and will not populate the People section in the Explore page.
smart_search_enabled_description: If disabled, images will not be encoded for smart search.
email_ignore_certificate_errors_descript: Ignore TLS certificate validation errors (not recommended)
memories_setting_description: Manage what you see in your memories
transcoding_advanced_options_description: Options most users should not need to change
video_hover_setting_description: Play video thumbnail when mouse is hovering over item. Even when disabled, playback can be started by hovering over the play icon.
display_original_photos_setting_descript: Prefer to display the original photo when viewing an asset rather than thumbnails when the original asset is web-compatible. This may result in slower photo display speeds.
smart_search_description: Search for images semantically using CLIP embeddings
permanent_deletion_warning_setting_descr: Show a warning when permanently deleting assets
show_in_timeline_setting_description: Show photos and videos from this user in your timeline
auto_launch_description: Start the OAuth login flow automatically upon navigating to the login page
two_pass_encoding_setting_description: Transcode in two passes to produce better encoded videos. When max bitrate is enabled (required for it to work with H.264 and HEVC), this mode uses a bitrate range based on the max bitrate and ignores CRF. For VP9, CRF can be used if max bitrate is disabled.
duplicate_detection_setting_description: Use CLIP embeddings to find likely duplicates
prefer_wide_gamut_setting_description: Use Display P3 for thumbnails. This better preserves the vibrance of images with wide colorspaces, but images may appear differently on old devices with an old browser version. sRGB images are kept as sRGB to avoid color shifts.
prefer_embedded_preview_setting_descript: Use embedded previews in RAW photos as the input to image processing when available. This can produce more accurate colors for some images, but the quality of the preview is camera-dependent and the image may have more compression artifacts.
watch_filesystem_setting_description: Watch external libraries for file changes
transcoding_required_description: Only videos not in an accepted format

past_durations.days: {count, plural, Past one {count day} other {{count, number} days}
past_durations.hours: {count, plural, Past one {count hour} other {{count, number} hours}
past_durations.years: {count, plural, Past one {count year} other {{count, number} years}

acceleration_qsv: Quick Sync (requires 7th gen Intel CPU or later)
bitrate_description: Videos higher than max bitrate or not in an accepted format
optimal_description: Videos higher than target resolution or not in an accepted format
no_favorites_message: Add favorites to quickly find your best pictures and videos
no_archived_assets_message: Archive photos and videos to hide them from your Photos view
no_assets_message: CLICK TO UPLOAD YOUR FIRST PHOTO
no_albums_message: Create an album to organize your photos and videos
no_shared_albums_message: Create an album to share photos and videos with people in your network
no_libraries_message: Create an external library to view your photos and videos
trash_no_results_message: Trashed photos and videos will show up here.
repair_no_results_message: Untracked and missing files will show up here
